- Sprint Review
In this sprint cycle, some key tasks were accomplished by the team, including sprint planning, design of the login screen and dashboard, 
as well as developing a preliminary prototype for the main features of the login and overall system.
The team was able to design a use case diagram, a class diagram, as well as a test plan.
The outcome of this sprint cycle was the creation of a preliminary prototype for the overall system,
which enabled the team to visualize the overall interface for users.
The diagrams enabled the team to comprehend the overall structure of the system as well as the interaction with users.

- Sprint Retrospective

What went well

The team worked well together and communicated well throughout the process. 
Most of the intended tasks were accomplished on time, and the design of the prototype helped in understanding how the system should work.

- Challenges

The greatest challenge was effective management of time and the coordination of tasks among the team members.
Some tasks required more discussion to ensure all members understood the system requirements and design.

- Improvements for next sprint

Improvements for the next sprint would be effective task allocation and the setting of deadlines for each task.
Communication would be more frequent in the next sprint.


